Themba Zwane of Mamelodi Sundowns challenged by Salulani Phiri and Edgar Manaka of Polokwane City during the Absa Premiership 2019/20 match between Mamelodi Sundowns and Polokwane City at the Loftus Versveld Stadium, Pretoria on the 21 December 2019 PRETORIA - Mamelodi Sundowns emerged victorious against Polokwane City in their Absa Premiership clash Pretoria. The game seemed to be headed for a goalless draw, but the title holders had another trick up their sleeve. READ: New Pirates coach off to a winning start Sibusiso Vilakazi came off the bench to net a goal that ultimately handed the hosts a 1-0 win. Sundowns are now six points behind log leaders Kaizer Chiefs who are in action on Sunday.